        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 28 at 2:54PM MDT until June 28 at 3:15PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 254 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles east of
Colony, or 15 miles northwest of Belle Fourche, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect damage
to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

Locations impacted include...
Northwestern Belle Fourche Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>Prepare immediately for large hail and deadly cloud to ground
lightning. Seek shelter inside a well-built structure. Stay away from
windows.</instruction>
